# ERPNext UI Architecture (Project Standard)

- Treat ERPNext styling as the default UI architecture for all pages.
- Reuse shared classes/components before creating page-specific styling.

## Required layout order

- `PageHeader` first.
- KPI cards row second (if needed).
- Unified filter toolbar third.
- Data table/list as the main content.

## Filter toolbar standard

- Use the shared toolbar pattern: `erp-filter-bar`.
- Date quick filters must use: `erp-date-seg` + `erp-date-seg-btn`.
- Range controls must use: `erp-filter-date` + `erp-filter-label`.
- Apply button must use: `erp-filter-apply`.
- Search must use: `erp-search-input` (or `erp-search-input--table`).
- Select filters must use: `erp-filter-select`.

## Responsive rules

- Mobile-first: avoid crowded inline controls.
- On small screens, wrap controls into clean rows with full-width important inputs.
- Keep tap targets clear and consistent with ERPNext spacing.

## Consistency guardrails

- Do not invent one-off filter/header systems per page.
- Prefer existing ERPNext utility classes in `App.css`.
- If a new shared UI pattern is needed, add it once in shared styles/components, then reuse everywhere.
